        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          For 2025, you can contribute up to <strong>CHF 7,056</strong> if you're employed with a 2nd pillar, or <strong>up to 20% of your net income (maximum CHF 35,280)</strong> if you're self-employed without a 2nd pillar. These contributions are fully tax-deductible, potentially saving you thousands in taxes annually.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          The tax savings depend on your income level and canton, but typically range from <strong>CHF 1,500-3,500 annually</strong> for employed persons and <strong>CHF 3,000-7,000</strong> for self-employed individuals without a 2nd pillar.
        </p>
      </div>
